{{Infobox Noble | name = Himuka no Kamuto Mirahime | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | era = [[Yayoi period]], [[Kojiki#Japan|Ancient times]] | birth_date = Unknown | death_date = Unknown | other_names = | posthumous_name = | divine_name = | dharma_name = | burial_place = | rank = | lord = | clan = | parents = | siblings = | spouse = [[Amihikata Kihikata no Mikoto]] | children = [[Takeihikatsu no Mikoto]], [[Nunakawami no Mikoto]] | notable = }}
'''Himuka no Kamuto Mirahime''' (日向賀牟度美良姫) is a woman mentioned only in the '''[[Sendai Kuji Hongi]]'''. If she existed, she would have been a person from the [[Yayoi period]], but her existence is considered questionable.
== Genealogy == She appears only in the '''[[Sendai Kuji Hongi]]'''. She is the mother of Takeihikatsu no Mikoto, the distant ancestor of the [[Miwa clan]], and Nunakawami no Mikoto, the empress of [[Emperor Annei]].
== Notes == {{Reflist}}
== Related topics == *[[Miwa clan]]
{{DEFAULTSORT:Himuka no Kamuto Mirahime}} [[Category:Ancient Japanese people]]

